member.summary:
Recursively splits provided amount into equal parts and tries get this value from the accounts that still can pay:
           if some account is unable to pay that equal part, the remainder will be spread between thouse that still can;
           i.e. three accounts with holdings 10, 100, 1000 will pay 10, 25, 25 respectively if requested value is 60.

Executes during first pass for interaction for all methods, used as early filtering
           for interactables  (to quickly skip undesired interactions). Requires InteractResult.Fail to exclude,
           InteractResult.NoOp will just do nothing for this check.

summary.p:
It is very rough estimate after all:


There no guarantee that another crafting component won't output to other not linked inventory;

There no guarantee that another crafting component won't contribute to another work order;

There no guarantee items counted in storages won't go to another work order or won't be picked up by player;

There no guarantee even within single order that counted items won't be used as another ingredient, because they may have match multiple ingredients
            (i.e. have multiple tags which matches different ingredients or may be used as specific item for one ingredient and match by tag for another ingredient).

member.sample:
This code creates Hewing Efficiency Module which modifies both resource and speed efficiency and only applies to values associated with HewingSkill.

class HewingEfficiency1 : EfficiencyModule
{
   public HewingEfficiency1() : base(ModuleTypes.ResourceEfficiency | ModuleTypes.SpeedEfficiency, typeof(HewingSkill), 0.9f) { }
}

member.summary:
            Tries to parse  from  string.
            It has following outputs:


if string is empty then  is null and failed without message;

if no matching command then  is null and failed with message about unknown command, command name removed from ;

if matching command without sub commands then  set to command and result is succeed, command name removed from ;

if matching command with sub commands and sub command name is empty then  set to command and result is failed without message, command name removed from ;

if matching command with sub commands and no matching sub command then  set to command and result is failed with message about unknown sub command, command name and sub command name removed from ;

if matching command with sub commands and matching sub command then  set to sub command and result is succeed, command name and sub command name removed from ;
